<br>
Get a healer buddy to get pretty close to the gate.  Healer casts celerity on your team and prepares group heal spamming.<br>
<br>
Get a few melee buddies and all port out at the same time.  Port back in.<br>
<br>
While waiting to port back in during the delay, swing at the nearest target, pop off your DDs, and hope your healer spams group heal if you are hit really hard in those few seconds.  Rinse, repeat.  With celerity plus instas, you can deal out some damage pretty quickly.<br>
<br>
- let one person go out a second sooner to get the target, everyone else uses /assist /face then DD/DD/swing, etc. (for skalds anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   With enough skalds, your instas alone can take down some targets. <br>
<br>
- Take a break after 2 or 3 to let the enemies focus go elsewhere...then start it back up.<br>
<br>
Do this enough, and if others are joining in (sbs, other tanks, etc.) you can sometimes cause enough distress, especially with a good guard pop, to drive them off the hill. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<br>
-Dane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/usplinterdaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Splinter DAOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/23/02 2:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: keep defense</span><hr size=1> /agree Dane<br>
<br>
The keep walls are definitely not a place for a skald.  We don't have the range for out dds; we become targets for dots, aes, nukes, stuns, etc.. and merely become a power drain for healers.  It's much more efficient and fun, yet dangerous, to pop in and out of the keep.<br>
<br>
I actually have one of my hotbars set up solely for popping in and out of keeps.  As soon as you pop out be sure to immediately hit /enter to get back in the keep as quickly as possible.  Another thing you may want to consider is creating separate macro's for exit and enter, as spamming one macro may end up porting you back outside when you don't want to be out there.<br>
<br>
I haven't used /assist on this, but have been considering it... just need to get enough people that know how to pop in and out without dying outside. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/23/02 5:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> keep defense</span><hr size=1> Stay in the courtyard, beg to get in the PBAE/GTAE caster group, rest song on, count the rps<br>
<br>
Get in the walls, use you 15gp, 2 min recast sapphire DF shield charge, inflicting a 3*60ish DoT on a random enemy, get stunned/nuked/shot to death in the process (don't laugh, I have killed one green con firby with that, who had a sliver of life left after a guard pull, that made my day).<br>
<br>
Get in the Lord room with your warrior and zerker friends, and play the in game dice and card game, waiting for the invaders to rush in (happened once in the inner dungeon of a relic keep under siege, no kidding, before we suicided and decided to organize a keep retaking force)<br>
<br>
Use exploits to hit people/siege engine from inside ???? (won't do it, condemn it ...)<br>
<br>
Popping in and out may be an option depending on the assaulting forces, but on my server, let's just say the hibernian zergs bring usually wayyyyy more people, and PBAE casters than necessary ...<br>
<br>
Aside from setting up a trebuchet if ye are defending one of the merchant keeps, there goes the role of the skald in a keep defense.<br>
But, hey, we have speed for solo ganking, and sinle group gank squad ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uaurensirramalot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AurenSirRamAlot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/24/02 5:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=332.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: keep defense</span><hr size=1> I typically cover the guys trying to nuke outside from the walls.  Assasin pops, i target and DD DD  mezz.<br>
